
Wow, I was impressed. "Still listening."
"And you're hair."
"What about my hair?"
"Even though you're dressed down, your hair looks like a personal stylist takes care of it. Either that or you're an expect at highlighting."
I smiled, fingering the loose curls that had fallen. There was the faintest tint of auburn red in it. It wasn't extremely noticeable because I did have a very good stylist. Very good and very expensive.
"Impressed?"
I shrugged causally. "Maybe."
He stood up again. All six foot and then some. "How about that walk?" He looked so sure of himself.
Why not? You only live once, right?
